==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic *''hwilo'', from Indo-European.  Cognate with Old High German ''[[wila|wīla]]'' (German ''[[Weile]]''), Old Saxon ''[[#Old Saxon|hwīl]]'' (Dutch ''[[wijl]]''), Gothic [[𐍈𐌴𐌹𐌻𐌰]], Old Norse ''[[hvíla]]'' (Swedish ''[[vila]]''), and cognate with the second element of Latin ''[[tranquillus]]''.

